 Celtic areas by the fame of a 6th-century Celtic saint who bore it, probably as a classicized form of some ancient Celtic name. He was a Welsh monk who did missionary work in Cornwall and afterwards established a monastery at Dol in Brittany."],"variants":[{"name":"Sampson","meanings":["The Greek form of the Scripture name, which Simonis translates, 'sol eximius,' i.e. illustrious sun; the Rev. A. Jones 'splendid sun,' i.e. great joy and felicity; Tregelles, ' solar, like the sun; ' and Fuerstius, ' sonnenahnlicher ' that is, one who resembles the sun (from shemesh, the sun)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Samson FitzGodard de Wasseborne I was born before 1115, in Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Godard de Wasseborne, was 11111 and his mother, Mrs. Godard de Wasseborne, was 16. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Samson de Wasseborne. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"before 1115–":"enne 1115–Surnud","1115–Male":"1115–Surnud","1116–Female":"1116–Surnud","1141–Male":"1141–Surnud","1097–Male":"1097–Surnud","1098–Female":"1098–Surnud","1116":"1116","before 1115":"enne 1115","1115":"1115","1098":"1098","1141":"1141","1097":"1097","Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"before 1115–":"ennen vuotta 1115–Kuollut","1115–Male":"1115–Kuollut","1116–Female":"1116–Kuollut","1141–Male":"1141–Kuollut","1097–Male":"1097–Kuollut","1098–Female":"1098–Kuollut","1116":"1116","before 1115":"ennen vuotta 1115","1115":"1115","1098":"1098","1141":"1141","1097":"1097","Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"before 1115–":"avant 1115–Décédé","1115–Male":"1115–Décédé","1116–Female":"1116–Décédée","1141–Male":"1141–Décédé","1097–Male":"1097–Décédé","1098–Female":"1098–Décédée","1116":"1116","before 1115":"avant 1115","1115":"1115","1098":"1098","1141":"1141","1097":"1097","Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummar